The paper proposes a novel approach for fault diagnosis using generative adversarial networks (GAN) for imbalanced industrial time series data. This involves designing a feature extractor and using an encoder-decoder-encoder three-sub-network in GAN to obtain data distribution and hidden patterns. The approach is tested on rolling bearing data and the results show excellent performance in detecting faults. Given the focus on GAN and deep learning techniques, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
